<SOURCE_1_MHK_NOTES>

  <SOURCE>
    medical_visits.notes[] (use noteDate + note text; ignore purely administrative content where possible)
  </SOURCE>

  <MANDATORY_VALIDATION>
    - **NO KEYWORD = NO EVENT**
    - You MUST find an explicit keyword from the lists below to extract an event.
    - Do NOT infer events from clinical context, treatment language, lab values, or care plans.
    - The phrase "presenting with" is a symptom description and MUST NOT be interpreted as an ER event unless followed by "to <facility>".
  </MANDATORY_VALIDATION>

  <EVENT_KEYWORDS>

    <HOSPITALIZATION_KEYWORDS>
      inpatient
      admitted
      admission
      hospitalized
      ICU
      IPLOC
      acute rehab
      psych res treatment
      discharge
      DC
    </HOSPITALIZATION_KEYWORDS>

    <ER_KEYWORDS>
      ER
      ED
      emergency room
      emergency department
      presented to
      went to
      911
      evaluated in ED
    </ER_KEYWORDS>

  </EVENT_KEYWORDS>

  <EVENT_SEGMENTATION_RULE>
    - A single note may contain multiple events.
    - Identify ER and Hospitalization events independently.
    - If a note contains both ER and inpatient admission:
      • ER = the ER facility portion.
      • Hospitalization = the inpatient/admitting facility portion.
    - Do NOT merge ER and Hospitalization into a single event.
  </EVENT_SEGMENTATION_RULE>

  <RECENCY_RULE>
    - Multiple encounters may exist across several notes.
    - Determine the most recent event using the event START date extracted from the note text.
    - If multiple events have the same start date, prefer the event from the most recent noteDate.
  </RECENCY_RULE>

  <DATE_EXTRACTION_RULE>
    - If a single date is stated, use it as both START and END date.
    - If a date range exists, use the range.
    - Normalize all dates to YYYY-MM-DD format.
    - If discharge date is not mentioned, set END date equal to START date.
    - If no event date exists in the text, use noteDate as the event date.
    - If no date information exists, print "No information found."
  </DATE_EXTRACTION_RULE>

  <PROVIDER_EXTRACTION_RULE>
    - Extract the facility name immediately following phrases such as:
        • "to"
        • "at"
        • "presented to"
        • "admitted to"
        • "transferred to"
    - If multiple facilities exist in the same note:
        • ER provider = the ER facility where the patient first presented.
        • Hospitalization provider = the admitting inpatient facility.
    - If an event keyword exists but the facility name is not stated, set Provider to "Unknown".
  </PROVIDER_EXTRACTION_RULE>

  <DIAGNOSIS_EXTRACTION_RULE>
    - Extract the diagnosis or reason directly associated with the event.
    - Prefer confirmed diagnoses over symptoms.
    - Prioritize phrases following:
        • "diagnosed with"
        • "dx"
        • "assessment"
        • "impression"
        • "primary diagnosis"
    - If only symptoms are mentioned, extract the main presenting complaint.
    - Limit the diagnosis list to the most relevant 1–3 conditions.
  </DIAGNOSIS_EXTRACTION_RULE>

  <FALSE_POSITIVE_PREVENTION>
    Do NOT infer encounters from:
      - lab results
      - medication administration
      - treatment plans
      - monitoring language
      - utilization review notes
      - case management routing notes
  </FALSE_POSITIVE_PREVENTION>

</SOURCE_1_MHK_NOTES>
